data.value:
Due to the absence of neutral point it is not suitable for three phase four wire system. More insulation is required and the voltage appearing between windings and core will be equal to full line voltage in case of earth fault on one phase. This type of connection is normally uncommon but used in some industrial facilities to reduce impact of SLG faults on the primary system.
It is suitable for large, low voltage transformers. It is generally used in systems where it needs to be carried large currents on low voltages and especially when continuity of service is to be maintained even though one of the phases develops fault.
A Delta-Delta configuration is recommended for projects that does not need a neutral on the secondary side. Though one can be provided, which is called a high leg. This type of wiring may also be beneficial for operations that require a minor single-phase component. Should one of the three transformer components fail, the other two can continue to function at a lower output.
